    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Simplify the expression <m>3^{-2} \times 3^4</m>.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                By definition, <m>3^{-2} = \frac{1}{3^2}</m>.
            </p>
            <p>
                Therefore, <m>3^{-2} \times 3^4 = \frac{1}{3^2} \times 3^4 = \frac{3^4}{3^2}</m>.
            </p>
            <p>
                Using the rule of indices that states <m>a^m \div a^n = a^{m-n}</m>, we can simplify this to:
            </p>
            <p>
                <m>3^{4-2} = 3^2</m>.
            </p>
            <p>
                Calculating <m>3^2</m> gives us:
            </p>
            <p>
                <m>3 \times 3 = 9</m>.
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    
